"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkcasdoor_website=globalThis.webpackChunkcasdoor_website||[]).push([[66],{65353(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"casdoor-joins-cncf-landscape","metadata":{"permalink":"/uk/blog/casdoor-joins-cncf-landscape","editUrl":"https://github.com/casdoor/casdoor-website/edit/master/i18n/uk/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2026-02-22-casdoor-joins-cncf-landscape.mdx","source":"@site/i18n/uk/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2026-02-22-casdoor-joins-cncf-landscape.mdx","title":"Casdoor Joins CNCF Cloud Native Landscape","description":"On February 22, 2026, Casdoor joined the CNCF Cloud Native Landscape, under the Security & Compliance category in Provisioning. The Landscape brings together widely used cloud-native projects and products; inclusion helps users and enterprises discover and evaluate solutions for building cloud-native systems.","date":"2026-02-22T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"Casdoor","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/casdoor"},{"inline":true,"label":"CNCF","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/cncf"},{"inline":true,"label":"Cloud Native","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/cloud-native"},{"inline":true,"label":"Landscape","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/landscape"},{"inline":true,"label":"IAM","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/iam"},{"inline":true,"label":"SSO","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/sso"},{"inline":true,"label":"Security","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/security"}],"readingTime":1.94,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Yang Luo","title":"Casdoor Maintainer","url":"https://github.com/hsluoyz","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/hsluoyz","key":"hsluoyz","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"casdoor-joins-cncf-landscape","title":"Casdoor Joins CNCF Cloud Native Landscape","authors":["hsluoyz"],"tags":["Casdoor","CNCF","Cloud Native","Landscape","IAM","SSO","Security"],"date":"2026-02-22T00:00:00.000Z"},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Enhancing App Security and User Experience with Casdoor Face Authentication SSO","permalink":"/uk/blog/face-authentication-casdoor-sso"}},"content":"On February 22, 2026, **Casdoor** joined the [CNCF Cloud Native Landscape](https://landscape.cncf.io/), under the **Security & Compliance** category in Provisioning. The Landscape brings together widely used cloud-native projects and products; inclusion helps users and enterprises discover and evaluate solutions for building cloud-native systems.\\n\\n[https://landscape.cncf.io/?item=provisioning--security-compliance--casdoor](https://landscape.cncf.io/?item=provisioning--security-compliance--casdoor)\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n<img src=\\"/img/blog/cncf-landscape-casdoor.png\\" alt=\\"Casdoor on CNCF Landscape - Security and Compliance section\\" style={{maxWidth: \'100%\', height: \'auto\', border: \'1px solid #eee\', borderRadius: \'8px\'}} />\\n\\n_Casdoor on the CNCF Cloud Native Landscape (Security & Compliance)_\\n\\n## About Casdoor\\n\\n<div style={{display: \'flex\', alignItems: \'center\', gap: \'1rem\', flexWrap: \'wrap\', marginBottom: \'1rem\'}}>\\n\\n<img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/casdoor-logo_1185x256.png\\" alt=\\"Casdoor\\" style={{height: \'80px\', width: \'auto\'}} />\\n\\n</div>\\n\\nCasdoor is an open-source, UI-first Identity and Access Management (IAM) / Single Sign-On (SSO) platform with a web UI. It supports OAuth 2.0, OIDC, SAML, and CAS, as well as many social logins (Google, GitHub, WeChat, etc.), and helps you build user management and SSO in a few steps. Casdoor is developed by [Casbin](https://casbin.org) in Golang and React. It uses a front-end/back-end separation architecture, supports high concurrency, and is actively maintained by the community. The project has received over 13k GitHub stars.\\n\\n## About CNCF and the Cloud Native Landscape\\n\\n<div style={{display: \'flex\', alignItems: \'center\', gap: \'1.5rem\', flexWrap: \'wrap\', marginBottom: \'1rem\'}}>\\n\\n<img src=\\"https://www.cncf.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/cncf-main-site-logo.svg\\" alt=\\"CNCF - Cloud Native Computing Foundation\\" style={{height: \'80px\', width: \'auto\'}} />\\n<img src=\\"https://landscape.cncf.io/images/logo_header.svg\\" alt=\\"CNCF Cloud Native Landscape\\" style={{height: \'80px\', width: \'auto\'}} />\\n\\n</div>\\n\\nThe **Cloud Native Computing Foundation (CNCF)** is a Linux Foundation project that promotes cloud-native technologies. Its vision is to make cloud native ubiquitous. CNCF maintains the **Cloud Native Landscape** ([https://landscape.cncf.io](https://landscape.cncf.io)), which classifies and tracks projects and products in the cloud-native ecosystem and serves as a reference map for developers and enterprises.\\n\\n## Looking ahead\\n\\nJoining the CNCF Landscape reflects progress in Casdoor\u2019s maturity and community. We will keep improving Casdoor and its integration with cloud-native workflows, and we welcome more users and contributors to join the community.\\n\\nRelated links:\\n\\n- [Casdoor](https://casdoor.org) \xb7 [GitHub](https://github.com/casdoor/casdoor) \xb7 [Documentation](https://casdoor.org/docs) \xb7 [CNCF Landscape \u2013 Casdoor](https://landscape.cncf.io/?selected=casdoor)"},{"id":"face-authentication-casdoor-sso","metadata":{"permalink":"/uk/blog/face-authentication-casdoor-sso","editUrl":"https://github.com/casdoor/casdoor-website/edit/master/i18n/uk/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2023-12-12-face-authentication-casdoor-sso.mdx","source":"@site/i18n/uk/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2023-12-12-face-authentication-casdoor-sso.mdx","title":"Enhancing App Security and User Experience with Casdoor Face Authentication SSO","description":"In an era where digital identity management is crucial, Single Sign-On (SSO) solutions like Casdoor are revolutionizing the way users interact with multiple applications. Casdoor\'s SSO simplifies the login process by allowing users to authenticate just once to access multiple services. This not only enhances user convenience but also boosts engagement and satisfaction.","date":"2023-12-12T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"Casdoor","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/casdoor"},{"inline":true,"label":"SSO","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/sso"},{"inline":true,"label":"Single-Sign-On","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/single-sign-on"},{"inline":true,"label":"Face Recogniztion","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/face-recogniztion"},{"inline":true,"label":"FaceID","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/face-id"},{"inline":true,"label":"Face","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/face"},{"inline":true,"label":"Machine Learning","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/machine-learning"}],"readingTime":1.61,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"James Lawson","title":"Product Manager","url":"https://casdoor.org","imageURL":"https://cdn.casbin.com/casdoor/static/admin.png","key":"James Lawson","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"face-authentication-casdoor-sso","title":"Enhancing App Security and User Experience with Casdoor Face Authentication SSO","authors":["James Lawson"],"tags":["Casdoor","SSO","Single-Sign-On","Face Recogniztion","FaceID","Face","Machine Learning"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Casdoor Joins CNCF Cloud Native Landscape","permalink":"/uk/blog/casdoor-joins-cncf-landscape"},"nextItem":{"title":"Welcome","permalink":"/uk/blog/welcome"}},"content":"In an era where digital identity management is crucial, Single Sign-On (SSO) solutions like Casdoor are revolutionizing the way users interact with multiple applications. Casdoor\'s SSO simplifies the login process by allowing users to authenticate just once to access multiple services. This not only enhances user convenience but also boosts engagement and satisfaction.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\nFor businesses, Casdoor\'s SSO streamlines user credential management, enhancing security and simplifying new user onboarding. It counters the risk associated with weak or recycled passwords by centralizing user management.\\n\\nHowever, in the face of growing online threats, integrating robust security measures in SSO systems like Casdoor is vital. This is where face authentication technology comes into play, adding an extra layer of protection while maintaining user-friendly interactions.\\n\\nFace authentication employs unique facial characteristics to confirm user identities. It compares live images with stored facial templates, offering a secure yet straightforward way to authenticate users. This method boasts high accuracy, even under varied conditions, and is widely adopted in modern consumer devices.\\n\\nIntegrating face authentication into Casdoor\'s SSO system promises a secure, efficient, and seamless user experience. To ensure optimal performance, it is crucial to focus on:\\n\\n1. _Anti-Spoofing Measures_: Implementing liveness detection, like tracking eye movements or random gestures, is essential to counteract spoofing attempts and maintain system integrity.\\n\\n2. _Regular Updates for Improved Accuracy_: Keeping the face authentication technology updated with the latest AI and biometric advancements ensures accuracy and enhances user experience. It\'s vital to use diverse datasets for algorithm training to prevent biases.\\n\\n3. _Balancing Security and Convenience_: The best systems strike a perfect balance between stringent security measures and user convenience. This approach encourages user adoption by ensuring a straightforward authentication process without compromising security.\\n\\nIn conclusion, by integrating face authentication with Casdoor\'s SSO, businesses can offer a secure, efficient, and user-friendly login experience. This not only fortifies security but also aligns with modern user expectations in the digital world."},{"id":"welcome","metadata":{"permalink":"/uk/blog/welcome","editUrl":"https://github.com/casdoor/casdoor-website/edit/master/i18n/uk/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2021-08-24-welcome.mdx","source":"@site/i18n/uk/docusaurus-plugin-content-blog/2021-08-24-welcome.mdx","title":"Welcome","description":"Welcome to Casdoor official website!\ud83d\udc4b","date":"2021-08-24T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"Casdoor","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/casdoor"},{"inline":true,"label":"SSO","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/sso"},{"inline":true,"label":"Authentication","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/authentication"},{"inline":true,"label":"OAuth2.0","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/o-auth-2-0"},{"inline":true,"label":"Casbin","permalink":"/uk/blog/tags/casbin"}],"readingTime":1.43,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"ErikQQY","title":"Casbin Member","url":"https://github.com/ErikQQY","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/52615090?s=120&v=4","key":"ErikQQY","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"welcome","title":"Welcome","authors":["ErikQQY"],"tags":["Casdoor","SSO","Authentication","OAuth2.0","Casbin"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Enhancing App Security and User Experience with Casdoor Face Authentication SSO","permalink":"/uk/blog/face-authentication-casdoor-sso"}},"content":"Welcome to Casdoor official website!\ud83d\udc4b\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## What is Casdoor?\\n\\nCasdoor is a UI-first [Identity Access Management (IAM)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Identity_management) / [Single-Sign-On (SSO)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single_sign-on) platform based on OAuth 2.0, OIDC, SAML and CAS.\\n\\nCasdoor is developed by [Casbin](https://casbin.org) using Golang and React.\\n\\nCasdoor aims at providing a powerful authentication platform to handle the user management.\\n\\n## Why use Casdoor?\\n\\n- \u26a1\ufe0f Powerful feature and simple config. With support for  <img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_google.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img> <img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_github.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img> <img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_facebook.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img> <img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_twitter.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img> <img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_linkedin.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img> <img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_weibo.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img> <img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_wechat.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img> <img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_qq.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img> <img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_dingtalk.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img>   <img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_gitee.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img>  <img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_wecom.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img><img src=\\"https://cdn.casbin.org/img/social_gitlab.png\\" width=\\"30\\"></img> sign in and traditional username/password sign in, Casdoor helps you implement your users management system just in a few steps.\\n\\n- \ud83d\udca5 Front-end back-end separation architecture. Casdoor provides maneuverable web UI and supporting high concurrency.\\n\\n- \ud83e\udd42 Active open source community. Casdoor is open source and actively maintained.\\n\\n- \ud83c\udf10 Multi-language support. Casdoor supports multiple languages, including Chinese, English, French, and many more.\\n\\n## How to use Casdoor?\\n\\nYou can follow the detailed document to learn about [Casdoor API](https://door.casdoor.com/swagger/) and [setup your own Casdoor](/docs/basic/server-installation). Or use the [Casdoor SDKs](/docs/how-to-connect/sdk) to implement your own application."}]}}')}}]);